In a speech at the National Education Association's representative assembly, President Joe Biden expressed his gratitude to educators for their dedication and hard work during the COVID-19 pandemic. He highlighted the importance of investing in education and outlined his plans to improve the education system in the United States. These plans include providing funding for school infrastructure, increasing support for educators, expanding access to high-quality preschool and community college, and extending the Child Tax Credit. Biden emphasized the role of teachers in shaping the future of the country and urged them to continue making a difference in the lives of their students. He concluded by stating that America's strength lies in its possibilities and that teachers play a crucial role in nurturing those possibilities.